decks.notes: The main focus of this deck is to utilize the Aggro strategy with Minsc, Beloved Ranger as the commander. The deck includes a wide variety of creatures, spells, and lands that support a fast and aggressive playstyle. Cards like Birds of Paradise, Llanowar Elves, and Devoted Druid help accelerate mana ramp, while creatures like Melira, the Living Cure and Voice of Resurgence provide resilience and protection. The inclusion of powerful spells like Swords to Plowshares and Lightning Bolt allow for removal of threats on the opponent's side. With a mix of efficient creatures and disruptive spells, this deck aims to overwhelm the opponent quickly and efficiently before they can establish their own game plan.

This deck focuses on utilizing Niv-Mizzet Reborn as the commander to generate card advantage and control the game through a diverse range of multicolored spells. The deck includes a variety of removal spells, counterspells, and card draw effects to disrupt the opponent's strategy and maintain a strong board presence. With a mix of powerful creatures like Baleful Strix and Tasigur, the Golden Fang, alongside versatile spells like Demonic Tutor and Force of Will, the deck is designed to adapt to different situations and outmaneuver the opponent. By efficiently utilizing the colors available in the deck and leveraging Niv-Mizzet Reborn's ability to draw cards, this control deck aims to outvalue and outsmart opponents in a duel commander format.

This Aggro deck built around Zimone and Dina focuses on early game aggression, using disruptive spells like Duress and Thoughtseize to control opponents' hands while deploying efficient threats like Elves of Deep Shadow and Tarmogoyf. The deck also includes powerful recursion cards like Reanimate and Grist, the Hunger Tide to continually bring back threats from the graveyard. With a variety of mana dorks like Llanowar Elves and Birds of Paradise, the deck ramps up quickly to cast its powerful spells and creatures. Additionally, utilizing cards like Contamination and Opposition to further disrupt opponents' strategies while taking advantage of Zimone's card draw ability to maintain resources and keep up the pressure on the opponent.
